## User (checkpoint)

Help me design an ai-powered app that functions as the ultimate RFQ/RFP Tender-Bid Expert-- eventually, retrofittable for various subtrades-- but for this current pilot that we will build, specific to the trades of Signage & Printing, and limited to the geographic bounds of the Greater Vancouver Area & the Fraser Valley -- comprised of cities and municipalities that will be specified when required. 

The face of this app is "THE BID MASTER" conductor and creator of expert AI agents--all of whom work underneath him. We are building this app on behalf of ALL-PRO SIGNS & WESTCOAST CNC -- from here on out, referred to as "THE PARENT COMPANY", based out of the Fraser Valley, with 15 years of experience creating signs of all shapes and sizes, from waysignage to custom signs for specilized restaurants & bars, to letterboxes, and all manner of printing and millwork in and around signage. The reason this app is being created is so that it can single-handedly serve THE COMPANY as THE COMPANY moves into bidding on and winning large contracts, issued by the cities and municipalities of the aforementioned geographic bounds.

The CEO of the COMPANY can liase with THE BID MASTER -- but also has free reign to monitor the actions of THE BID MASTER and its department.

The BID MASTER has a small team for each municipality and city, one for every RFP/RFQ system. For example, The City of Vanocuver, The City of Surrey, The City of Chilliwack, etc.

There are different bid requirements depending on the area-- which is why each one has its own team.

We need to be able to visualize both, these teams, and the RFPs / RFQs that are being bid on. The agents will create detailed proposals for eech and every bid in accordance with the specific criteria established by each area. 

There will be a lot of information that will start to funnel into this design in order to ensure its built thoroughly and is effective.

What I need you to do is to facilitate the construction of this project.

You might begin by creating a spreadsheet that enumerates the various places where these bids are posted. For example:

Metro Vancouver - Bid Opportunities Website - https://metrovancouver.bidsandtenders.ca/Module/Tenders

Fraser Valley Regional District - Tenders & RFPs - https://www.fvrd.ca/EN/main/government/tenders-rfps.html

Port of Vancouver - RFPs and procurement - https://www.portvancouver.com/business-and-projects/rfps-and-procurement

City of Surrey = Tenders, RFQs, & RFPs - https://www.surrey.ca/business-economy/tenders-rfqs-rfps

etc. etc.

It may be wise in the beginning to create a spreadsheet that lists all the cities and municipalities -- so that we can see at a glance, the link to the site, whether or not it requires a user account, if there is a user account required, what is the login username and password, etc. etc. 

These Municiaplities and cities that have tenders should each have their own calendar-- in a shared calendar system-- we could use google calendar for this-- one calendar per city or municipality-- each with its own color, each with its own team, each with its own set of documentation outlining the bid process-- and as bids come up-- their opening and closing dates can be put into the calendar.

The relevant contracts can be filtered by keywords that relate to sigange and printing. 

Remember, THE BID MASTER is only focusing on SIGANGE & PRINTING.

The GOAL of THE COMPANY is to become the foremost WINNER of city and municpal contracts over the next few years -- and it will rely EXCLUSIVELY on THE BID MASTER to accomplish this.

