# Tier 2: High Priority Municipalities

## Overview

Tier 2 municipalities represent significant bid opportunities with medium-to-high volume. These jurisdictions typically generate **2-4 relevant opportunities per month** and receive strong resource allocation.

---

## Tier 2 Members

| Municipality | Team ID | Portal Type | Estimated Monthly Opportunities |
|--------------|---------|-------------|--------------------------------|
| City of Burnaby | TEAM-BUR | BidsAndTenders | 3-5 |
| City of Richmond | TEAM-RIC | Direct Website | 2-4 |
| City of Coquitlam | TEAM-COQ | BidsAndTenders | 2-4 |
| Township of Langley | TEAM-TOL | BidsAndTenders | 2-4 |
| City of Abbotsford | TEAM-ABB | BidsAndTenders | 2-3 |
| Vancouver Airport (YVR) | TEAM-YVR | Custom Portal | 2-4 |
| Port of Vancouver | TEAM-POV | Direct Website | 2-3 |

---

## Resource Allocation

### Agent Configuration
- **Scout Agent:** 30-minute scan intervals (standard)
- **Analyst Agent:** Standard processing, full analysis
- **Writer Agent:** Standard templates with municipal customization
- **Compliance Agent:** Standard review process

### Human Oversight
- Weekly review by BID MASTER
- Bi-weekly CEO summary
- Escalation for contracts >$100K

---

## Success Metrics

| Metric | Target |
|--------|--------|
| Bid Detection | 100% within 8 hours |
| Response Rate | 75%+ of relevant opportunities |
| Win Rate | 30%+ |
| Revenue Target | 30% of total contract value |

